overview: The user initiated a project to enhance their Sleep Questionnaire
  Application by adding a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for
  data access, and an authentication system. The assistant evaluated the
  existing codebase against the SOW, identifying the need for a new Prisma model
  for questionnaire responses, API routes for data handling, and a client-facing
  dashboard. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) for the database
  and implementing a simple password-based authentication. Initially, a custom
  session management system was developed, but it was later refined to leverage
  Next.js middleware for more streamlined route protection. The implementation
  covered updating demographics, creating database schema, building API
  endpoints, and developing the admin dashboard with CSV export. The entire
  system was successfully tested, confirming questionnaire submission, admin
  login, and data retrieval.
